		{
			"type": "action",
			"name": "Crashing Slam Down",
			"system": {
				"actionType": {
					"value": "action"
				},
				"description": {
					"value": "<p>You make an attack to knock a foe off balance, then follow up immediately with a sweep to topple them. Make a melee Strike. If it hits, Urnak automatically apply the critical success effect of a [[/act trip options=action:crashing-slam-down]] . If you're wielding a two-handed melee weapon, you can ignore Trip's requirement that you have a hand free. If you used a two-handed melee weapon for the Strike, you can use the weapon's damage die size instead of the regular die size (@Damage[ 1d12[bludgeoning]]]) for the damage from a critical Trip. Both attacks count toward your multiple attack penalty, but the penalty doesn't increase until after you've made both of them.</p>",
					"gm": ""
				},
				"publication": {
					"title": "",
					"authors": "",
					"license": "OGL",
					"remaster": false
				},
				"rules": [
					{
						"key": "AdjustDegreeOfSuccess",
						"selector": "athletics",
						"predicates": "action:crashing-slam-down",
						"adjustment": {
							"all": "to-critical-success"
						}
					},
					{
						"key": "Note",
						"selector": [
							"athletics"
						],
						"title": "{item|name}",
						"outcome": [
							"criticalSuccess"
						],
						"predicate": [
							"action:crashing-slam-down"
						],
						"text": "If you used a two-handed melee weapon for the Strike, you can use the weapon's damage die size instead of the regular die size (@Damage[ 1d12[bludgeoning]]]) for the damage from a critical Trip"
					}
				],
				"slug": "crashing-slam-down",
